<front>
<div type="abstract"><head>Rat an Frankfurt am Main und Mainz</head><p>Der Rat übersendet die Abschrift eines Briefs über König Sigismund und die Geschehnisse in Böhmen.</p>
</div>
<!--This div could possibly contain the analytic portion of the edition.-->
<div type="linguisticAnalysis"><ab><w join="" lemma="" msd="" part="" pos=""><fLib><f name=" "/></fLib></w></ab></div>
</front>
<body><div type="diplomatic"><pb facs="#facs_357" id="177v"/><!--The following div is the container for the adress lines of the letter.-->
<div type="addressee"><ab facs="#facs_357_r1l3">Den von Frankenfurt </ab>
</div>
<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content"><ab facs="#facs_357_r1l4"><expan>L<ex>ieben</ex></expan> <expan>fr<ex>ewnde</ex></expan> als Jr vns nehſt <expan>verſchr<ex>iben</ex></expan> vnd gebetten habt . <expan>eẅr<ex>er</ex></expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_357_r1l5"><expan>weıſh<ex>eit</ex></expan> / <expan>ʒuu<ex>er</ex>ſchreıben</expan> / Ob wır von <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex>s</expan> <expan>gnedıgıſt<ex>en</ex></expan> <expan>h<ex>er</ex>ren</expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_357_r1l6">~ des <expan>Römıſche<ex>n</ex></expan> etc kunıgs <expan>gelegenh<ex>eit</ex></expan> vnd den lewffen ʒu </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_357_r1l7">Beheım ıcht treffenlıchs <expan>v<ex>er</ex>neͣmen</expan> . Alſo tun wır <expan>eẅr<ex>er</ex></expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_357_r1l8"><expan>fürſıchtık<ex>eit</ex></expan> ʒu <expan>wıſſ<ex>en</ex></expan> . daʒ eınem <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex>m</expan> guten freẅnde bey vns </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_357_r1l9">ın kürcʒ eın brıef <expan>kome<ex>n</ex></expan> ıſt von <expan>eine<ex>m</ex></expan> guten freẅnde . der </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_357_r1l10">Jm etwas treffenlıch vnd <expan>eygenl<ex>ich</ex></expan> dauon <expan>verſchr<ex>iben</ex></expan> hat als </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_357_r1l11">Jr an der <expan>yngeſloſſ<ex>en</ex></expan> <expan>abſchr<ex>ift</ex></expan> <expan>deſſ<ex>elben</ex></expan> <expan>br<ex>iefs</ex></expan> / dıe wır eẅch in </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_357_r1l12"><expan>ſundr<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>gut<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>freẅntſch<ex>aft</ex></expan> <expan>ſchık<ex>en</ex></expan> wol <expan>v<ex>er</ex>nemen</expan> <expan>w<ex>er</ex>det</expan> . Denn </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_357_r1l14">wo wır <expan>eẅr<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>erſamk<ex>eit</ex></expan> lıeb <expan>od<ex>er</ex></expan> dıenſt etc </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_357_r1l15"><expan>Dat<ex>um</ex></expan> <expan>f<ex>er</ex>ıa</expan> v<hi rend="sup">a</hi> <expan>an<ex>te</ex></expan> Nıcolaȷ </ab>
</div>
<div type="similiter"><ab facs="#facs_357_r1l16">Den von Maıncʒ <expan>ſı<ex>mi</ex>l<ex>ite</ex>r</expan> </ab>
</div>
</div><div type="regularised"><pb facs="#facs_357" id="177v"/><!--The following div is the container for the adress lines of the letter.-->
<div type="addressee">
<ab>Den von Frankenfurt</ab>
</div>
<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content">
<ab><expan>L<ex>ieben</ex></expan>
<expan>fr<ex>eunde</ex></expan>, als ir uns nehst
                                <expan>verschr<ex>iben</ex></expan> und gebetten habt,
                                <expan>ewr<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>weish<ex>eit</ex></expan>
<expan>zu v<ex>er</ex>schreiben</expan>, ob wir von
                            <expan>uns<ex>er</ex>s</expan>
<expan>gnedigist<ex>en</ex></expan>
<expan>h<ex>er</ex>ren</expan> des <expan>römische<ex>n</ex></expan> etc.
                        kunigs <expan>gelegenh<ex>eit</ex></expan> und den lewffen zu Beheim icht
                        treffenlichs <expan>v<ex>er</ex>neͣmen</expan>, also tun wir
                                <expan>ewr<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>fürsichtik<ex>eit</ex></expan> zu <expan>wiss<ex>en</ex></expan>, daz
                        einem <expan>uns<ex>er</ex>m</expan> guten frewnde bey uns in kürcz ein
                        brief <expan>kome<ex>n</ex></expan> ist von <expan>eine<ex>m</ex></expan>
                        guten frewnde, der im etwas treffenlich und
                            <expan>eygenl<ex>ich</ex></expan> davon
                            <expan>verschr<ex>iben</ex></expan> hat, als ir an der
                                <expan>yngesloss<ex>en</ex></expan>
<expan>abschr<ex>ift</ex></expan>
<expan>dess<ex>elben</ex></expan>
<expan>br<ex>iefs</ex></expan>, die wir ewch in
                            <expan>sundr<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>gut<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>frewntsch<ex>aft</ex></expan>
<expan>schik<ex>en</ex></expan>, wol <expan>v<ex>er</ex>nemen</expan>
<expan>w<ex>er</ex>det</expan>. Denn wo wir <expan>ewr<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>ersamk<ex>eit</ex></expan> lieb <expan>od<ex>er</ex></expan> dienst
                        etc. <expan>Dat<ex>um</ex></expan>
<expan>f<ex>er</ex>ia</expan> v<hi rend="sup">a</hi>
<expan>an<ex>te</ex></expan> Nicolai.</ab>
</div>
<div type="similiter">
<ab>Den von Maincz <expan>si<ex>mi</ex>l<ex>ite</ex>r</expan>.</ab>
</div>
